== Original Works ==

This build derives from several projects.

[https://retrobrewcomputers.org/doku.php?id=builderpages:muellerk:start Another Build - Multicomp Z80 with b/w Graphics - by muellerk] adds a monochrome bitmapped display functionality to the [https://www.retrobrewcomputers.org/doku.php?id=builderpages:rhkoolstar:mc-2g-1024 Z80 Multiboot version of Multicomp by rhkoolstar] which was based on [http://searle.x10host.com/Multicomp/index.html Grant Searle's Multicomp].

Our build of [https://github.com/douggilliland/MultiComp/tree/master/MultiComp_On_RETRO-EP4CE15/Multicomp-MPM Z80 Multiboot version of Multicomp by rhkoolstar].

This build runs on a [https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32949281189.html?spm=a2g0o.productlist.0.0.23c6239dgIvRTF&algo_pvid=18ecb5a7-9379-4a8d-9987-d234c882a467&algo_expid=18ecb5a7-9379-4a8d-9987-d234c882a467-2&btsid=0b0a555c16163265169281511efa18&ws_ab_test=searchweb0_0,searchweb201602_,searchweb201603_ QMTECH EP4CE15 FPGA card] mounted to a [http://land-boards.com/blwiki/index.php?title=RETRO-EP4CE15 RETRO-EP4CE15].

== Introduction ==

This graphics expansion consists of two parts, the [https://github.com/douggilliland/MultiComp/tree/master/MultiComp_On_RETRO-EP4CE15/multicomp-z80_vhdl_3xtty_1xvga/Microcomputer_3xTTY_1xVGA modified multicomp-z80 VHDL-code] and [https://github.com/douggilliland/Retro-Computers/tree/master/Z80/Software/multicomp-z80_xgraph an RSX-package, that holds the needed software to handle the graphic output (dots, lines etc., bitmaps and text)]. Incl. are also several demo programs used to create the shown screenshots.

